The Cause: When you tried to log in, your frontend tried to send an API request to http://localhost:3000 via your vite.config.js proxy. However, because the frontend is now running inside a Docker container, localhost:3000 was looking inside the frontend's own container for the backend instead of reaching out to the Backend container! Because no backend was found, it returned an empty connection error, which broke your .json() parser!

